instruct_text: Welcome to the Job Simulator Task!
In this task, you will read 16 stories. During each one you will simulate having one job.
This job will be assigned to you before each story.
While reading each story, you should imagine yourself as having that job.
There are 8 possible jobs you could be asked to simulate.
In addition, your task will be to answer job-related questions.
There are four question per job.
You will have to try to memorize these questions and then remember your answers to the questions.
You will be asked about the answers to these questions at end of the experiment.
In order to help you memorize the questions, there will be a short quiz on them before the actual task begins.
In addition, before each story, there will be a reminder of what these questions are.
Press the space bar to begin learning the jobs and the questions for each one.

Q1: What is the grocery store like upon entering?
Q2: What items do the clients pick out?
Q3: How is the checkout line and how long do the clients wait in line?
Q4: How much are the groceries and what method of payment do the clients use?
D1: How long does it take for the cashier to scan all of the customers’ groceries?
D2: What type of grocery bags do the clients use?

Q1: What is the grocery store like upon entering?
Q2: What items do the clients pick out?
Q3: How is the checkout line and how long do the clients wait in line?
Q4: How much are the groceries and what method of payment do the clients use?
D1: How long does it take for the cashier to scan all of the customers’ groceries?
D2: What type of grocery bags do the clients use?

Q1: When the clients arrive at the airport, how much time do they have to go through?
Q2: What do the clients have do at security to comply with the security check?
Q3: How do the clients feel when they are  walking to the gates?
Q4: Where does each client sit on the plane?
D1: Are the security guides friendly or rude?
D2: Are the airport restrooms clean?

Q1: How does the person who is initiating the breakup feel before they do it?

D1: Does the person being broken up with expect that this is coming?
D2: For how long has the initiator been wanting to break up?
